body:
@revans2 Okay. I didn't realize that had changed, I'm okay with either approach.

One thing I did notice is that the documentation dropdown is missing from the home page, and the downloads page is now a 404.

(sorry for hijacking this pull request)

@revans2 It was a caching issue. Sorry for the noise.

I agree with @harshach, we may want to consider a redirect from downloads.html to release.html to keep from breaking external links and bookmarks.

I think we need to add a link to the KEYS file for releases, and it might help to add maven information like we did in the old downloads page.

@vesense 
Could we apply standard batching behavior among external modules?
I mean, this PR doesn't flush when batch size is set to 100 but there're 99 tuples in several hours, while storm-hbase, storm-hive, and more flushes batch when tick tuple is received, and it sets tick tuple interval.

@vesense 
I'd really like to add that change in this issue, since it's not hard to address.
Btw, totally agreed about abstracting batch process to something common.
